I am sorry about that :disappointed:. They serve very delicious food here please have a look at these.
Can you show me the varieties of the 1st image?
Yup! Why not. Have a look at these steaming hot momos :wink:. Aren't these amazing.
Can you tell the filling of the 1st and 5th image?
The 1st one is filled with tandoori chicken and the 5th image is filled with vegetables. :stuck_out_tongue:
Great then I will definitely go with the 1st one. :grin: Can you show their best noodles?
Oh!!! These are the best noodles which are handmade. :wink:
I  am allergic to the ingredients in the 2nd image:no_mouth:
Oh, I am sorry! Let me show you other images.
These looks really good :yum: Can you suggest some side-dishes in non-veg to go with the 3rd image?
Along with the 3rd image, people prefer having soups :wink:
Nope :-1: I don't like soups. Do you have anything else?
These are the next best thing which you can have. I hope you'll like these :slightly_smiling_face:.
I prefer the 2nd image, but is it very spicy?
I have some in less spicy also :slightly_smiling_face: have a look these are made with the same ingredients as in 2nd image.
I am not sure if these will go with the noodles. Anyways can you tell the price of the noodles and the appetizer?
:slightly_smiling_face: On total for the noodles and the appetizers, it will cost you around 200/- Rs only.
Yeahhh its really cheap:smiley:.  Do they deliver?
Yeah, they do deliver! But I would suggest you to visit the place once so that you can enjoy a hot meal. :wink:
Sure but I am not very happy :frowning: with the ambience. So how do they charge for delivery?
I sorry about the ambience :disappointed:. They charge Rs 30 extra for the delivery :hugging_face:
Fine its totally affordable :blush:, So how much time do they take to deliver?
It takes 30 minutes max. :slightly_smiling_face:
Great :+1: I suppose I can wait for some tasty food. :heart_eyes:
Oh! That's so nice. Do you want any other information :thinking_face:.
Nope I am done for today. Thanks for your assistance :blush:
You are welcome! :grinning:
